ce:section.ce:para:
Co-CDs: Cobalt(

                           ii

                        ) gluconate was calcined at 240 °C for 2 h under nitrogen atmosphere. The obtained gray-brown solid was stirred in aqueous solution for 1 h. The clear liquid was collected by filtration and freeze-dried to obtain Co-CDs.
